    <jsp:include page="/views/partials/header.jsp"/>
  <h1 class="head">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <img src="img/privacy.png" alt="" class="imgPrivacy">
  <section class="sec1">
    <h2 class="sub-head1">Introduction</h2>
    <div class="intro">
        
        <p class="intro-details">We value the trust you place in us when you use our services. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of personal information we collect, how we use it, and the steps we take to ensure your data is protected. By using our services, you consent to the practices described in this policy.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec2">
    <h2 class="sub-head">Types of data We collected</h2>
    <div class="type">
        <div class="type-set">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Personal Information</h2>
            <ul class="person-info">
                <li>Name, address and contact</li>
                <li>Health records</li>
                <li>Payment details</li>
                <li>Employment details for healthcare providers</li>
            </ul>
            <img src="img/persona.png" alt="" class="type-img">
        </div>
        <div class="type-set">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Usage Data</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail"> Explain if any data is automatically collected, such as usage patterns, device information, IP addresses, and login times.</p>
            <img src="img/usage.png" alt=""  id="img2">
        </div>
        <div class="type-set">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Sensitive Data</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">Clearly state that sensitive personal data (e.g., health-related information) is collected and explain the necessary safeguards in place.</p>
            <img src="img/sense.png" alt=""  id="img3">
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec3">
    <h1 class="sub-head">How We Collect Your Information</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Direct interactions</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">Information you provide when registering for services, booking appointments, or communicating with us</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Automated technologies</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">To manage patient records, process payments, and handle billing and insurance claims.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Third-party sources</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">Information we may obtain from external sources, such as insurance companies or healthcare providers, to process claims or verify patient details</p>
        </div>
       
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec4">
    <h1 class="sub-head">How We Use Your Information</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Providing healthcare services</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">To deliver medical treatment, manage appointments, and ensure the quality of care</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Administrative functions</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">To manage patient records, process payments, and handle billing and insurance claims.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Improvement of services</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">To analyze system performance, improve patient experience, and enhance the functionality of our Hospital Management System.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Legal compliance</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail"> To comply with applicable healthcare regulations, such as HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) or GDPR (General Data Protection Regulation), where applicable</p>
        </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec4">
    <h1 class="sub-head">Sharing Your Information</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Third-party service providers</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail"> We share information with third-party providers who assist us with operational functions, such as billing, insurance verification, cloud storage, and IT services.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Legal and regulatory requirements</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">We may disclose your personal data when required to do so by law, including in response to a subpoena, legal process, or regulatory request
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Business transfers</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale, your personal information may be transferred to the new owner</p>
        </div>
       
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec4">
    <h1 class="sub-head">Data Security</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Encryption</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail"> All sensitive data, such as health records and payment information, is encrypted during transmission and storage</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Access control</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">Access to your personal information is restricted to authorized personnel only, based on their roles
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Regular audits</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">We conduct regular security audits to identify and address vulnerabilities.</p>
        </div>
       
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec4">
    <h1 class="sub-head">Data Retention</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type3">
            
            <p class="sub-head-detail">We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, comply with legal obligations, and resolve any disputes. The retention period will be determined based on the type of data and legal requirements.

                Once data is no longer needed, we will securely delete or anonymize it to ensure privacy</p>
        </div>
        
       
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec4">
    <h1 class="sub-head">Your Rights</h1>
    <div class="collect">
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Access</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail"> You can request a copy of the personal information we hold about you</p>
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Correction</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">You can request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete data.
        </div>
        <div class="collect-type">
            <h2 class="sub-head2">Deletion</h2>
            <p class="sub-head-detail">You may request the deletion of your personal information, subject to legal obligations.
                Opt-out: You may opt-out of certain communications, such as marketing messages.</p>
        </div>
       
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="sec6">
    <h1 class="sub-head3"> Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h1>
    <div class="det">
        <p class="detail">Our system may use cookies and other tracking technologies to enhance your experience. Cookies are small text files stored on your device to help us improve functionality, analyze system performance, and provide a personalized experience.

            You can manage cookies through your browser settings, but disabling cookies may impact the functionality of the Hospital Management System.
            
            </p>
    </div>
    
  </section>
  <section class="sec6">
    <h1 class="sub-head3">Childrenâ€™s Privacy</h1>
